block append vars
  - var page = ConfDocs.DOCS.find('atom.html')

block append main
  p.
    This style guide imports styles from the Xmeter stylesheet.
    See the
    #[a(href="https://cdn.rawgit.com/chharvey/xmeter/master/docs/atom.html") Xmeter style guide]
    for more information.

//- block append main
  p.
    This stylesheet imports a library called
    #[cite Bangs!], which is a set of atoms for all properties and values.
    Only the most common classes are listed below, however feel free to check out
    #[a(href="https://github.com/chharvey/bangs/blob/gh-pages/PROPERTIES.md") the comprehensive list.]
  section#-fl
    h2 Floats
    p.
      Use floats to float content to the left or to the right in surrounding prose.
      Please do not use these classes to create entire page layouts.
    figure.docs-figure
      div.-fl-l: u floating left
      div.-fl-r: u floating right
      div.
        Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.
        Aliquam sagittis suscipit nunc, a cursus libero euismod at.
        Nulla placerat neque massa, quis interdum leo efficitur vel.
        Donec feugiat varius arcu non volutpat.
        Mauris eget mauris ut mauris auctor mattis id vel justo.
        Nulla dictum arcu nec suscipit mollis.
        Maecenas a iaculis nisl, ut pretium est. Nulla facilisi.
      pre.
        &lt;div class="#[u -fl-l]"&gt;floating left&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="#[u -fl-r]"&gt;floating right&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor ...&lt;/div&gt;
  section#-w
    h2 Widths
    p.
      Use these classes to set the width of block (or inline-block) elements.
      These can be very useful for items in a grid object.
    p.
      Percentage widths are fluid, best for responding to screen size.
      Pixel widths are absolute, best for when you know the exact width.
      Em widths are adjustable, based on the font size of the element
      (e.g. if the element&rsquo;s font size is 16px, then 1em is 16px
      and 5em is 80px).
