    p.
      You may add a breakpoint suffix, for using these classes only in certain
      media breakpoints. For example, to set the width of an element to 50%,
      but only for the medium screen breakpoint (larger than 45em), use class
      #[code .-w-1o2-sM].
      The suffix #[code -sM] stands for medium screen.
      The following table displays breakpoint suffixes and their meanings.
    pre.
      ‹no suffix›    all media queries (screen, print, etc.)
      -s             screen only, all sizes
      -sK               small screens and up (greater than 30em/ 480px)
      -sM              medium screens and up (greater than 45em/ 720px)
      -sG               large screens and up (greater than 60em/ 960px)
      -sT             x-large screens and up (greater than 75em/1200px)
      -sP            xx-large screens and up (greater than 90em/1440px)
      -p             print only
      -h             on hover and on focus only
